IS  - 2
SP  - 125
EP  - 138
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/06/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(78)90002-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387878900020
AB  - This paper develops a Keynesian model of the Portuguese economy in which the prices of the sectors of final demand are derived from input-output relationships. This model is used for short-run simulation analysis of the Portuguese economy through 1977. It is seen that Portugal cannot simply rely on world demand for its exports to improve its balance of payments and to generate an export-led recovery. Simulation of a policy package which includes a devaluation and fiscal restraint indicates that this policy will improve the external current account and raise domestic savings.
ER  - 

